## Responsiveness Testing and Iteration Across Devices

The website was tested across multiple screen sizes using Chrome DevTools (F12 → Toggle Device Toolbar). Screenshots below show the site responding correctly at each breakpoint after testing and adjustments.

### Mobile — 375 × 812px

 Replace this line with your screenshot: `![Mobile 375px](images/responsiveness/mobile-375px.png)`

Observations at this breakpoint:
- Hamburger navigation menu replaces horizontal nav links
- All grids collapse to a single column
- CTA buttons stack vertically and span full width
- Hero heading reduces to a smaller font size
- Baker card stacks avatar above text content

---

### Tablet — 768 × 1024px

Replace this line with your screenshot: `![Tablet 768px](images/responsiveness/tablet-768px.png)`

Observations at this breakpoint:
- Navigation switches to hamburger menu
- Feature cards and product grid display in two columns
- Enquiry form panel stacks (info panel moves below form)
- Footer displays in a two-column grid

---

### Tablet — 1024 × 768px

 Replace this line with your screenshot: `![Tablet 1024px](images/responsiveness/tablet-1024px.png)`

Observations at this breakpoint:
- Two-column grid layouts active
- Horizontal navigation bar visible
- Enquiry layout switches to single column
- Footer changes from four columns to two columns

---

### Desktop — 1440 × 900px

 Replace this line with your screenshot: `![Desktop 1440px](images/responsiveness/desktop-1440px.png)`

Observations at this breakpoint:
- Full three-column product and features grids active
- Four-column footer grid displayed
- Full horizontal navigation with animated underline hover effect
- Two-column enquiry layout (info panel left, form right)
- About story two-column layout (text left, image right)

---

> **How to add screenshots:**
> 1. Open your website in Chrome
> 2. Press **F12** → click the device toolbar icon
> 3. Set the width to each size above and take a screenshot
> 4. Save them into `images/responsiveness/` in your repo
> 5. Delete the `>` instruction lines above and the images will display automatically

